page.title: 14WILD LIFE
page.content: BECAUSE OUR AREA IS IN THE COUNTRY, THERE IS LOTS OF WILD LIFE AROUND, WE HAVE DONE A SURVEY OF THE WILD ANIMALS AND BIRDS THAT CHILDREN IN THE CLASS HAVE SEEN, AND THESE ARE THE RESULTS.THE ANIMALS MOST SEEN WERE HEDGEHOGS,MOLE AND RABBITS. NEXT WERE WATER RATS.NEXT HARES.OTHER ANIMALS SEEN WERE DOOR MOUSES,BATS, FIELD MOUSES,DEERS,SNAKES,RED SQUIRRES,SHREWS,WATER VOLE,OTTERS AND BEAVER.THE BIRDS MOST SEEN WERE 1ST SPARROW,ROBIN,BLACKBIRD.2ND WREN,BLUE TIT,HOUSE MARTIN,THRUSH.3RDGREAT TIT, GREENFINCH,STARLING,SWALLOW.4TH BULL FRINCH,ROOK.OTHER BIRDS SEEN WERE WOODPECKER,KINGFISHER,BLACK CAP AND SPOTTEDFIYCATCHER.
